==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|fr}} {{term|bergamote|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|it}} {{term|bergamotta|lang=it}}; probably a corruption of {{etyl|tr}} {{term|beg armudı||a lord's pear|lang=tr}}.

===Pronunciation===
*{{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈbɝɡəˌmɒt/}}

===Noun===
{{infl|en|noun}}

# {{botany}} A tree of the Orange family (''Citrus bergamia''), having a roundish or pear-shaped fruit, from the rind of which an essential oil of delicious odor is extracted, much prized as a perfume. Also, the fruit. 
# {{botany}} A variety of mint (''Mentha aquatica'', variety ''glabrata'').
# The essence or perfume made from the fruit.
# A variety of pear. -[[Johnson]].
# A variety of snuff perfumed with bergamot.
#:''The better hand . . . gives the nose its '''bergamot'''.'' - [[w:William Cowper|William Cowper]].
# A coarse tapestry, manufactured from flock of cotton or hemp, mixed with ox's or goat's hair; -- said to have been invented at Bergamo, Italy.  [[w:Encyclopedia Britannica|Encyclopedia Britannica]].

